QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarAttachmentsEmptyLine1: Use this tab to upload multimedia files that may be referenced in the questionnaire.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarAttachmentsEmptyLine2: To avoid slow synchronization we recommend combined size of all attached files not to exceed 2MB. For supported file types, formats, and dimensions

QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarLookupEmptyLine1: Use this tab to define lookup tables.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarLookupEmptyLine2: A lookup table provides reference information that may be queried by a key and used in enabling conditions and validation expressions.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarLookupEmptyLine3: A lookup table consists of a name and the lookup file, which may contain multiple tab-delimited columns of numeric values.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarMacroEmptyLine1: Use this tab to define macro substitutions.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarMacroEmptyLine2: A macro is a named expression that can be used in enabling conditions and validation expressions. A macro consists of name and content.

QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCriticalityConditionsEmptyLine1: Use this tab to define critical rules.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCriticalityConditionsEmptyLine2: Each critical rule consists of a condition and a message. Critical conditions may refer to any questions or variables and must be satisfied (evaluate to true). Treatment of interviews with unsatisfied critical conditions is determined during import of the questionnaire to the data server.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCriticalityConditionsEmptyLine3: Include a message for the interviewer (respondent) to explain what needs to be changed in the interview (the message is displayed when the critical condition is not satisfied). Including hyperlinks to questions in the message is useful for navigation.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarScenarioEmptyLine1: Use this tab to view your scenarios.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarScenarioEmptyLine2: A scenario is a snapshot of tester state, you can save it on tester by click on button "Save Scenario".
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarTranslationsEmptyLine1: Use this tab to manage questionnaire translations.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCategoriesEmptyLine1: Use this tab to manage reusable categories.

QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCategoriesEmptyLine2: You may download and update categories.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarTranslationsEmptyLine3: Translation will be applied on original texts and override values. You may leave some texts empty to use default original translations.
QuestionnaireEditor.SideBarCategoriesEmptyLine3: will be added to list of reusable categories for any types of categorical questions

QuestionnaireEditor.HelpConditionExpression: A logical expression that activates(deactivates) the current item depending on the answers on the other questions.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpExpression: A logical expression that is calculated depending on the answers on the other questions.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpFixedTitles: Number of items determines the roster size. Each element of the list corresponds to a title of the roster row. Each element of the list should be placed on a separate line.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpHideIfDisabled: By default, a disabled item is grayed-out. Checking this option will hide a disabled question or section on a tablet.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpRosterDisplayMode:
Sub-Section - the questions of the roster are shown behind the buttons corresponding to roster instances.
Flat - the questions of the roster are shown in the same level separated by headers corresponding to roster instances.
Table - the questions of the roster are shown in the same level as rows and columns of the table. 
Matrix - a categorical question of the roster is displayed as matrix. 
Table and Matrix views are supported only in Web survey, tablet falls back to 'Sub-Section' mode.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpHideInstructions: By default, an instruction text is shown on a tablet. Checking this option will show only the first line of instructions. Tapping on that line will show the complete text.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpInstruction: Instruction text that will be attached to the question.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpIsTimestamp: This option allows the user to stamp the current time on tablet
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpDefaultDate: This date will be shown as started date for selection on a tablet
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpDoNotExport: Mark this variable to exclude it from export
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpMask: Formatted entry for alpha-numerical values: phone numbers, ID codes, etc. Examples:"~" - Represents an alpha character (A-Z,a-z), "#" - Represents a numeric character (0-9), "*" - Represents an alphanumeric character (A-Z,a-z,0-9). "##/##/####" - date, "(###) ###-####" - phone number, "AA####" - flight number operated by American AirLines or "~*-###-~###"
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpSourceQuestion: Source question (answer generates number of rows)
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpUseFormatting: When checked, the numeric field on the tablet will be formatted as: d,ddd,ddd.dd, "d" represents digits (0-9), “,”(comma) is a thousand separator, and "." (dot) is a decimal point symbol.  Thousand separator and the decimal point symbol may vary for tablets with different cultures.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpValidationExpression: A logical expression that validates an answer to the current question. Might include values of other questions.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpValidationMessage: Error or warning message is shown when validation condition evaluates to "False" or error occurs during expression evaluation.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpVariableDescription: Text that will be shown next to a variable for testing purposes
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpVariableLabel: A text up to {{maxLength}} characters that will be attached to the exported variable.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpVariableName: Variable names and roster IDs may be from {{minLength}} to {{maxLength}} characters long and must contain only following characters: a-z, A-Z, _, or 0-9. The first character cannot be 0-9 or _ and the last one cannot be _.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpAttachmentName: The name of attachment file that will be displayed.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpCoverPage: The first section of every questionnaire contains identifying questions that are also displayed at the interviewers' and supervisors' dashboards.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpVirtualCoverPage:
Cover is virtual section that shows all identifying questions.
    Questions cannot be changed in this section

QuestionnaireEditor.HelpCriticalityConditionExpression: A logical expression that evaluates the interview as a whole to determine whether it satisfies the critical rules (when this expression evaluates to "True"). It may refer to any questions or variables.
QuestionnaireEditor.HelpCriticalityConditionMessage: This message is shown when the critical condition evaluates to "False" or an exception occurs during expression evaluation. The message may utilize hyperlinks and text substitution.
